lace lower than ye;"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asfl","text_ar":"اسفل"},{"kind":"text","text":"being here an adv. n.: or, as some read,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asofalu minokumo","text_ar":"اَسْفَلُ مِنْكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being lower than ye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b2-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vum~a radadonaAhu A^asofala saAfiliyna","text_ar":"ثُمَّ رَدَدْنَاهُ اَسْفَلَ سَافِلِينَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xcv. 5], means (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then we rendered him the lowest of low:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we reduced him to extreme old age,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decrepitude:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a state of perishing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing away:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a state of error;"},{"kind":"text","text":"relating to him who has disbelieved; (M, K;) for every infant is born of the natural constitution with which he is created in his mother's womb, and he who disbelieves and errs is reduced to this state: (M:) or the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we have made him to be of the people of the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Hell"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we have made him to go down"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the fire"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of Hell"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Bd.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufolay muDara","text_ar":"سُفْلَي مُضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The lower of Mudar"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said to denote"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those of Mudar with the exception of Kureysh and Keys:"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuloyaAmuDara","text_ar":"عُلْيَامُضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Elw","text_ar":"علو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sufolN","text_ar":"سُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b5-  The pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAfilu","text_ar":"اَسَافِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, parts"},{"kind":"text","text":"of valleys [&c.]. (TA.) The phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kilaAbu AlA^asaAfili","text_ar":"كِلَابُ الاَسَافِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurs in a verse of Aboo-Dhu-eyb as meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The dogs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the lower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, parts of the valleys."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"young ones"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels. (As, S, * TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}